The paper proposes a novel architecture for fine-grained categorization using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on interpretability, which is a key aspect of explainable AI (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for classification also falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of cropping and feature fusion, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
